# Financial Risk Capital Adequacy Borrowings Amount

## identifier
de5546

## type
float

## definition
Report the value of borrowings, plus overdrafts determined under stress test scenarios in accordance with the Capital Adequacy prudential standards. This method differs from the Australian Accounting Standards.

Borrowings are amounts of money on loan from financial institutions or other creditors with the promise or understanding that it will be repaid.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=FinancialRisk.CapitalAdequacy.Borrowings.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.05
- period=instant
